      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JETSETTER JACK (5) has just found one better in two runs back from a spell, well backed last time at Cranbourne when no match for an impressive winner. That looks a good form race and 1400m should be ideal now. Well placed to go one better. FOXSKY (2) has placed in his past two, giving a good sight but no match for a very impressive winner at Cranbourne last time out. He's on the quick turnaround and will take plenty of catching. HANDSOME MISSILE (3) is going well and will be hitting the line off a good tempo. LAUNDERING (6) was okay on debut at Sale when getting back over 1206m. Up in trip suits this son of Contributor much better, look for improvement.",
